 NativeBehavior NativeBehaviorSignature.attachBehavior(long address)
          Creates and attachs to the specified address of a native method a native instance of a predefined class implementing the interface NativeBehavior Current implementation calls NativeBehaviorSignature.attachBehavior(NativeAddress,long) with offset set to 0.
 NativeBehavior NativeBehaviorSignature.attachBehavior(NativeAddress address, long offset)
          Creates and attachs to the specified address and offset of a native method a native instance of a predefined class implementing the interface NativeBehavior With this object the native method can be called from Java using this signature.
